                        <item xml:id="e1">- The word ድንግል፡ (“Virgin”) is written (in black ink, by the scribe) in the upper margin of <locus target="#47v">47v</locus>; the word በከመ፡ (“Like, as”) is written upside down (in black ink, by the scribe) in the bottom margin of <locus target="#48v">48v</locus>.&#xD;
- Several names are written in red ink in the same hand as the main text on <locus target="#56r">56r</locus>, at the end of the text: [ወለ]ተ፡ ተክለ፡ ሃይማኖት፡ [ገብ]ረ፡ ተክለ፡ ሃይማኖት፡ ወልደ፡ ማርያም።, [Wälä]ttä Takla  Hāymānot, [G]äbrä Takla Hāymānot, Walda Māryām.&#xD;
- A note mentioning the title ውእቱ፡ ሰአታት፡ ዘቤተ፡ ክርስትያን፡ “This is the Hours of the church”, and a personal name in Latin script, Kahsay, are written (recently; in pencil) on <locus target="#57r">57r</locus>.&#xD;
- The title of the work (ሠአታት) is written in pen in the upper margin of <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>.&#xD;
- A simple black line is used as text divider on <locus target="#50v">50v</locus> and 56r.&#xD;
- Corrections (words or letters) are written interlineally and in the margins: <locus target="#14v">14v</locus>, 54v.&#xD;
- Immediate corrections indicated by thin lines above and below the word: <locus target="#5r">5r</locus>, 48r.&#xD;
- Erasures: <locus target="#8r">8r</locus>, 10r.&#xD;
- Crude minor notes: <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>, 19v, 20v, 22r, 23r, 25v, 26r, 29r, 30v, 33v, 34r, 57v.&#xD;
- Crude drawing on <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>.</item>
